# Agent Discipline

- Read surrounding code before editing; match naming, imports, and error-handling patterns.
- Smallest correct diff; no drive-by refactors or new abstractions unless required.
- No placeholders in delivered code: no `TODO`, `...`, stub bodies, or "implement later".
- Verify dependencies exist in `package.json` / `pyproject.toml` before importing new packages.
- Interface-first for new modules: types/contracts before implementation.
- Prefer editing existing files over creating parallel helpers.
- Concrete error messages; reuse project error types — no generic catch-all handlers.
- No over-commenting, generic names, or unnecessary wrappers.
- **Branches, commits, PR titles:** follow [`docs/open-source/NAMING_CONVENTIONS.md`](../../docs/open-source/NAMING_CONVENTIONS.md) so CI passes.
- Staged Markdown is auto-fixed on commit (`lint-staged` + markdownlint `--fix` in pre-commit).
- Run validation before claiming done: `pnpm lint`, `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm build`.
